{
  "stem": "71.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's why, you know, if we-- I would have jumped on the other side, I would have been in a crematorium.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they took us out, and then my third sister came, and we hugged and kissed.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they told us to go.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They-- they formed-- they put us all together and they took us to another camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were on the C lager.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They took us to A lager.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we were there I think two nights-- to nights and-- two nights and two days.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they brought in a group of Hungarian girls.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They gave us blankets to cover up.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was cold already.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was like November or October, I think.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the girls came-- the girls that came after us, they took the blankets, and they tore them apart and made themselves wrappings or whatever.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "When the [GERMAN] saw that, they took them outside.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And my sister was told to them-- a woman came in that worked in that A lager, and she called a name.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I said to her, I worked with your father.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So she became very befriended with us, because I gave her regards from her father, who was an older man.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And she called my younger sister on the side and said, Ruth, if they take you out at night kick, scream, bite, do anything you can, but don't stay.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "See that you can escape because when they take out, she says, at night, it goes directly to the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And here they're taking us out-- out at night and she got so hysterical she cried and she-- Ruth, what happened?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She would not tell us what happened.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She cried so bitterly, so that she really got hysterical.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
